  <title translate="true">Acceleration-Nominal</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword translate="true">Motion Definition:<keyword translate="true">Nominal Acceleration</keyword></keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="" style="text-align:left; text-indent:0px; margin-top:0px; margin-right:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; line-height:1.00; background-color:transparent; white-space:normal; page-break-inside:auto; page-break-after:auto; border:none; tabstops:none;"><table styleclass="MotionPupup" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box2" translate="true">Nominal Acceleration</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> is the acceleration as defined by the mathematical function of the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MT-Motion-Laws" styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">Motion-Law</link><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> and the Blend-Point motion-values. The </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">nominal acceleration</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> is shown in the Acceleration Graph. </text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">Machine elements will </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">always</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> experience accelerations significantly more than the </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">nominal acceleration</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">. If there is a step change in acceleration, the actual acceleration can be two times, and even more, than the nominal values.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
